Aston Villa stunned Old Trafford faithfuls on Saturday with a solid victory against Manchester United. In a match that saw many missed chances, the final minutes produced a perfect twist. Also Read: Man Utd Crash Out Of League Cup Defender, Kortney Hause had put Villa ahead with a powerful header two minutes from the end of normal time. However, the defender handled inside the box to present Manchester United with a lifeline. However, Bruno Fernandes blazed high over the bar in front of the Stretford End as United’s unbeaten start to the Premier League season came to an end.